00:58:17,244 --> 00:58:19,455
Come on. Look alive, big boy.

792
00:58:34,095 --> 00:58:35,429
[SOFTLY] Careful.

793
00:58:38,933 --> 00:58:41,977
-Careful.
-DEAN: Step up. Step up.

794
00:58:43,979 --> 00:58:45,481
[GATE OPENING]

795
00:58:49,902 --> 00:58:50,945
[GRUNTS]

796
00:58:51,112 --> 00:58:52,738
[YELLING]

797
00:58:54,949 --> 00:58:56,283
[WHOOPING]

798
00:59:01,080 --> 00:59:02,081
[GRUNTING]

799
00:59:05,000 --> 00:59:06,252
[GRUNTS]

800
00:59:10,005 --> 00:59:11,674
[LAUGHING]

801
00:59:16,554 --> 00:59:18,204
Where you going? Where you going?

802
00:59:21,058 --> 00:59:22,351
[WHARTON YELLING]

803
00:59:22,852 --> 00:59:24,145
Ain't this a party now?

804
00:59:24,478 --> 00:59:25,778
Is it or what? Let him go.

805
00:59:25,980 --> 00:59:27,731
DEAN: Shoot him. Shoot! See who you hit.

806
00:59:27,815 --> 00:59:29,441
DEAN: Shoot the son of a bitch.
Come on, shoot me!

807
00:59:29,525 --> 00:59:30,567
Shoot him!

808
00:59:30,651 --> 00:59:33,153
Hit him, Percy! God damn it! Hit him.

809
00:59:33,237 --> 00:59:34,905
Hit me, you limp noodle.

810
00:59:34,989 --> 00:59:35,989
Hit him, Percy!

811
00:59:36,073 --> 00:59:37,240
God damn it, hit him!

812
00:59:37,324 --> 00:59:38,784
Come on, Percy. Hit me.

813
00:59:38,868 --> 00:59:40,410
Wharton, I'm warning you.

814
00:59:40,494 --> 00:59:42,120
You warning me? Warn me now.

815
00:59:42,204 --> 00:59:43,413
PAUL: I'm warning you!

816
00:59:43,497 --> 00:59:45,499
-You're warning me?
-DEAN: Shoot him!

817
00:59:45,833 --> 00:59:47,334
Well, come on... [GRUNTS]

818
00:59:49,003 --> 00:59:50,253
[PANTING]

819
00:59:50,337 --> 00:59:51,546
[CLICKS SAFETY ON]

820
00:59:51,630 --> 00:59:52,965
[GROANS]

821
00:59:53,841 --> 00:59:54,967
You're a big fucker.

822
00:59:56,218 --> 00:59:57,386
Where'd you come from?

823
00:59:57,470 --> 00:59:58,679
[GRUNTS]

824
00:59:59,805 --> 01:00:01,015
[DEAN GRUNTING]

825
01:00:08,189 --> 01:00:10,440
BRUTAL: Come on, Dean.
Come on, boy, get up.

826
01:00:10,524 --> 01:00:12,474
[GASPING] All right. Now, just breathe.

827
01:00:12,943 --> 01:00:15,070
That's it. Just breathe. Just breathe.

828
01:00:17,031 --> 01:00:18,949
Breathe. Breathe, boy.

829
01:00:19,033 --> 01:00:20,450
DEAN: Didn't see it coming.
Come on, boy, breathe.

830
01:00:20,534 --> 01:00:22,119
DEAN: Didn't see it coming.

831
01:00:22,203 --> 01:00:24,079
Come on. Just breathe.

832
01:00:26,916 --> 01:00:28,876
We thought he was doped.

833
01:00:30,336 --> 01:00:33,714
Didn't we?
Didn't we all of us think he was doped?

834
01:00:33,798 --> 01:00:35,466
You didn't ask?

835
01:00:36,842 --> 01:00:38,636
Well, I guess that's not a mistake

836
01:00:39,220 --> 01:00:42,056
you'll be needing to make
again any time soon, is it?

837
01:00:56,403 --> 01:00:59,603
You go get Dean and Harry looked at.
Make sure they're all right.

838
01:01:00,533 --> 01:01:03,410
Percy, you make the report
to the warden for me.

839
01:01:04,203 --> 01:01:05,829
Start out by saying the
situation's under control.

840
01:01:05,913 --> 01:01:06,913
It's not a story.

841
01:01:06,997 --> 01:01:09,750
He will not appreciate you
drawing out the suspense.

842
01:01:09,834 --> 01:01:12,252
Well, what about you?
You're about ready to collapse.

843
01:01:12,336 --> 01:01:15,339
Ah, I've got the Mile
till you all come back.

844
01:01:16,423 --> 01:01:17,967
Go on, now. Go.

845
01:01:23,681 --> 01:01:24,890
[GRUNTS SOFTLY]

846
01:01:26,100 --> 01:01:29,103
BRUTAL: Come on, boy.
Let's get you looked at.

847
01:01:33,774 --> 01:01:35,474
-[DOOR CLOSES]
-[BREATHING HEAVILY]

848
01:01:54,837 --> 01:01:57,798
COFFEY: Boss,
I needs to see you down here.

849
01:02:01,802 --> 01:02:05,222
This is not a good time, John Coffey…

850
01:02:05,306 --> 01:02:07,265
Not a good time at all.

851
01:02:07,349 --> 01:02:11,353
But I needs to see you, boss.
I needs to talk to you.

852
01:02:11,896 --> 01:02:13,147
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

853
01:02:18,485 --> 01:02:20,446
[GRUNTING]

854
01:02:33,667 --> 01:02:34,835
Closer.

855
01:02:35,502 --> 01:02:37,702
Boss, you know you ain't
supposed to do that.

856
01:02:39,131 --> 01:02:41,091
Mind your business, Del.

857
01:02:50,851 --> 01:02:52,853
What do you want, John Coffey?

858
01:02:53,812 --> 01:02:55,262
[WHISPERING] Just to help it.

859
01:02:58,692 --> 01:03:00,152
COFFEY: Don't be afraid.

860
01:03:00,653 --> 01:03:01,737
Help!

861
01:03:02,529 --> 01:03:05,282
Help! John Coffey's
killing Boss Edgecomb!

862
01:03:05,532 --> 01:03:07,117
Help!

863
01:03:07,201 --> 01:03:08,786
What are you doing?

864
01:03:08,911 --> 01:03:10,496
DEL: Help!

865
01:03:13,040 --> 01:03:14,708
Boss Howell! Help!

866
01:03:15,626 --> 01:03:17,576
[GRUNTS] Boss Stanton! Somebody, come!

867
01:03:17,711 --> 01:03:19,713
Help!

868
01:03:21,423 --> 01:03:22,967
[PAUL GRUNTING]

869
01:03:27,638 --> 01:03:28,889
[SCREAMS]

870
01:03:32,726 --> 01:03:35,770
DEL: Help!

871
01:03:35,854 --> 01:03:38,190
Help! Boss Howell! Boss Stanton!

872
01:03:38,565 --> 01:03:41,484
Somebody, come!
John Coffey's killing Boss Edgecomb!

873
01:03:41,568 --> 01:03:43,904
Del, for Christ sakes, shut up!

874
01:03:44,738 --> 01:03:45,864
[COFFEY COUGHING]

875
01:04:30,784 --> 01:04:32,870
What did you just do to me?

876
01:04:34,997 --> 01:04:36,582
I helped it.

877
01:04:37,750 --> 01:04:39,376
Didn't I help it?

878
01:04:40,461 --> 01:04:42,254
I just took it back, is all.

879
01:04:43,589 --> 01:04:45,466
Awful tired now, boss.

880
01:04:46,592 --> 01:04:47,926
Dog-tired.

881
01:05:12,451 --> 01:05:15,204
DEL: Boss, what that man do to you?

882
01:05:38,560 --> 01:05:40,270
[UNZIPPING]

883
01:05:42,147 --> 01:05:44,525
[URINATING]

884
01:05:55,369 --> 01:05:56,870
[SIGHS]

885
01:06:01,208 --> 01:06:03,085
[SIGHS HEAVILY]

886
01:06:04,169 --> 01:06:06,380
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING ON RADIO]

887
01:06:17,891 --> 01:06:20,352
Hey, honey. How you feeling?

888
01:06:22,479 --> 01:06:24,690
Oh, not too bad.

889
01:06:26,400 --> 01:06:27,600
What did the doctor say?

890
01:06:30,529 --> 01:06:32,322
Oh, you know doctors.

891
01:06:32,739 --> 01:06:34,575
Gobbledygook, mostly.

892
01:06:35,617 --> 01:06:37,077
Gobbledygook.

893
01:06:49,089 --> 01:06:50,591
[CLICKS TONGUE]

894
01:06:52,259 --> 01:06:53,886
Having stew tonight.

895
01:07:04,104 --> 01:07:05,856
What are you doing?

896
01:07:12,738 --> 01:07:14,615
What does it feel like?

897
01:07:15,282 --> 01:07:17,618
Well, I know what it feels like.

898
01:07:21,580 --> 01:07:23,457
It feels great.

899
01:07:32,674 --> 01:07:35,302
-[JAN MOANING]
-[BED CREAKING]

900
01:07:42,726 --> 01:07:45,145
[PAUL MOANING]

901
01:07:50,150 --> 01:07:51,401
JAN: Mmm.

902
01:07:57,741 --> 01:07:59,493
Paul. Yeah?

903
01:08:00,077 --> 01:08:03,288
Not that I'm complaining… Uh-huh.

904
01:08:03,997 --> 01:08:07,542
But we haven't gone four times
in one night since we were 19.

905
01:08:07,626 --> 01:08:09,419
Yeah, we did, at your mom's, yeah.

906
01:08:09,503 --> 01:08:10,796
Mmm-hmm.

907
01:08:11,797 --> 01:08:14,007
Wanna tell me what's going on?

908
01:08:14,091 --> 01:08:15,342
[PANTING]

909
01:08:17,427 --> 01:08:18,845
Well…

910
01:08:20,347 --> 01:08:22,099
See, the thing is…

911
01:08:23,642 --> 01:08:26,728
I never actually made it in
to Dr. Bishop's yesterday.

912
01:08:30,190 --> 01:08:32,651
Brutal, Paul. Listen.

913
01:08:33,151 --> 01:08:35,570
I'm thinking of taking
the morning off sick.

914
01:08:35,654 --> 01:08:37,698
You cover the fort for me?

915
01:08:38,699 --> 01:08:40,992
That's swell. Thanks.

916
01:08:41,076 --> 01:08:43,953
Yeah, no. [STAMMERING]
I'm sure I'll feel better.

917
01:08:44,037 --> 01:08:45,914
Okay. Okay.

918
01:08:52,045 --> 01:08:53,695
You're sure you ought to do this?

919
01:08:55,632 --> 01:08:57,551
I'm not sure what I'm sure of.

920
01:09:14,693 --> 01:09:17,112
Burt, you got some company.

921
01:09:18,363 --> 01:09:20,114
Can I offer you a cold drink?

922
01:09:20,198 --> 01:09:22,868
Oh, yes, ma'am.
A cold drink would be fine. Thank you.

923
01:09:23,618 --> 01:09:24,869
Mr. Hammersmith, your office said

924
01:09:24,953 --> 01:09:26,829
I might find you at home today.

925
01:09:26,913 --> 01:09:28,582
Hope I'm not troubling you.

926
01:09:29,249 --> 01:09:31,417
Well, that depends, Mr…

927
01:09:31,501 --> 01:09:35,589
Paul Edgecomb. I'm E Block
supervisor up on Cold Mountain.

928
01:09:36,840 --> 01:09:38,341
The Green Mile.

929
01:09:38,425 --> 01:09:41,386
Yeah, I've heard of it.
Lost a few clients your way.

930
01:09:42,262 --> 01:09:43,972
I'd like to ask you about one of 'em.

931
01:09:44,056 --> 01:09:46,099
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

932
01:09:46,183 --> 01:09:48,143
Have a seat. Thank you.

933
01:09:52,814 --> 01:09:53,940
Which client?

934
01:09:54,024 --> 01:09:55,275
[CLEARS THROAT]

935
01:09:56,151 --> 01:09:58,570
Now you got my curiosity aroused.

936
01:09:59,154 --> 01:10:00,488
John Coffey.

937
01:10:00,572 --> 01:10:01,572
Ah.

938
01:10:01,656 --> 01:10:03,199
Coffey.

939
01:10:03,283 --> 01:10:04,576
He causing you problems?

940
01:10:04,951 --> 01:10:06,536
No. No, can't say he is.

941
01:10:06,620 --> 01:10:08,746
He doesn't like the dark
and cries on occasion,

942
01:10:08,830 --> 01:10:10,540
but other than that…

943
01:10:10,624 --> 01:10:13,919
He cries, does he?
Well, got a lot to cry about, I'd say.

944
01:10:14,252 --> 01:10:15,796
You know what he did.

945
01:10:16,505 --> 01:10:18,298
I read the court transcript.

946
01:10:19,508 --> 01:10:20,508
Thank you, missus.

947
01:10:20,592 --> 01:10:21,802
My pleasure.

948
01:10:23,220 --> 01:10:26,223
Kids! Lunch is about ready.
Y'all come on up.

949
01:10:26,556 --> 01:10:27,932
BOTH: Coming, Mama!

950
01:10:28,016 --> 01:10:31,103
What exactly are you trying to find out?

951
01:10:31,812 --> 01:10:34,512
I've wondered if he ever
did anything like that before.

952
01:10:35,607 --> 01:10:37,567
Why? Has he said anything?

953
01:10:37,651 --> 01:10:40,362
No, but a man who does a thing like that

954
01:10:41,154 --> 01:10:43,239
has often developed
a taste for it over time.

955
01:10:43,323 --> 01:10:45,116
It occurred to me

956
01:10:45,200 --> 01:10:47,785
that it might be easy enough
to follow his back trail.

957
01:10:47,869 --> 01:10:49,162
Find out.

958
01:10:49,830 --> 01:10:53,333
A man his size, and colored to
boot, can't be that hard to trace.

959
01:10:53,875 --> 01:10:57,128
You'd think so, but you'd be wrong.

960
01:10:57,212 --> 01:10:59,381
Believe me, we tried.

961
01:11:00,090 --> 01:11:01,740
Like he'd dropped out of the sky.

962
01:11:03,093 --> 01:11:04,677
How can that be?

963
01:11:04,761 --> 01:11:06,596
We're in a depression.

964
01:11:06,680 --> 01:11:08,931
A third of the country's out of work.

965
01:11:09,015 --> 01:11:10,933
People are drifting by the thousands,

966
01:11:11,017 --> 01:11:13,269
looking for jobs, for greener grass.

967
01:11:13,353 --> 01:11:16,553
Even a giant like Coffey wouldn't
get noticed everywhere he goes.

968
01:11:17,315 --> 01:11:19,609
Not until he kills
a couple of little girls.

969
01:11:20,485 --> 01:11:21,862
He is, uh

970
01:11:22,446 --> 01:11:24,489
strange, I admit.

971
01:11:24,865 --> 01:11:28,660
But there doesn't seem to be
any real violence in him.

972
01:11:29,619 --> 01:11:32,080
I know violent men, Mr. Hammersmith.

973
01:11:32,164 --> 01:11:34,207
I deal with them day in and day out.

974
01:11:35,917 --> 01:11:37,126
You didn't come up here to ask me

975
01:11:37,210 --> 01:11:38,669
whether he might have killed before.

976
01:11:38,753 --> 01:11:41,303
You came up here to see
if I think he did it at all.

977
01:11:43,091 --> 01:11:44,718
-Do you?
-[THUNDER RUMBLING]

978
01:11:46,052 --> 01:11:48,304
One seldom sees a less ambiguous case.

979
01:11:48,388 --> 01:11:50,515
He was found with
the victims in his arms.

980
01:11:50,599 --> 01:11:52,267
And yet you defended him.

981
01:11:53,393 --> 01:11:55,479
Everyone is entitled to a defense.

982
01:11:56,521 --> 01:11:58,314
CYNTHIA: Kids! Lunch!

983
01:11:58,398 --> 01:11:59,898
Y'all listen to your mama now!

984
01:12:04,237 --> 01:12:06,198
I'll tell you something.

985
01:12:06,907 --> 01:12:09,075
And you listen close, too,
because it might be something

986
01:12:09,159 --> 01:12:10,660
you need to know.

987
01:12:10,744 --> 01:12:12,078
I'm listening.

988
01:12:13,455 --> 01:12:14,581
We had us a dog.

989
01:12:15,624 --> 01:12:17,708
Just a sweet mongrel.

990
01:12:17,792 --> 01:12:19,294
You know the kind.

991
01:12:20,754 --> 01:12:24,090
Well, in many ways, a good
mongrel dog is like a Negro.

992
01:12:24,966 --> 01:12:26,718
You get to know it.

993
01:12:27,052 --> 01:12:31,472
Often, you get to love it.
It is of no particular use,

994
01:12:31,556 --> 01:12:34,517
but you keep it around
because you think it loves you.

995
01:12:34,601 --> 01:12:36,228
[CHUCKLES]

996
01:12:36,603 --> 01:12:38,187
If you're lucky, Mr. Edgecomb,

997
01:12:38,271 --> 01:12:40,815
you never have to find out any different.

998
01:12:41,775 --> 01:12:43,375
My wife and I were not so lucky.

999
01:12:45,946 --> 01:12:47,489
Caleb, come here for a second.

1000
01:12:48,823 --> 01:12:50,158
Come here.

1001
01:12:51,493 --> 01:12:52,744
Please, Son.

1002
01:12:54,329 --> 01:12:56,248
He still has the one good eye.

1003
01:12:58,166 --> 01:13:00,543
I suppose he's lucky

1004
01:13:00,627 --> 01:13:02,712
not to be completely blind.

1005
01:13:05,674 --> 01:13:09,177
We get down on our knees and
thank God for that much at least.

1006
01:13:10,136 --> 01:13:11,596
Right, Caleb?

1007
01:13:13,974 --> 01:13:15,392
Okay, go on in now.

1008
01:13:16,142 --> 01:13:17,602
[DOOR OPENING]

1009
01:13:17,686 --> 01:13:18,769
[DOOR CLOSING]

1010
01:13:18,853 --> 01:13:21,565
That dog attacked my boy for no reason.

1011
01:13:22,357 --> 01:13:24,359
Just got it in his mind one day.

1012
01:13:25,318 --> 01:13:26,903
The same with John Coffey.

1013
01:13:26,987 --> 01:13:31,157
He was sorry afterwards.
Of that I have no doubt.

1014
01:13:31,908 --> 01:13:33,910
But those little girls

1015
01:13:33,994 --> 01:13:36,162
stayed raped and murdered.

1016
01:13:37,080 --> 01:13:39,082
Maybe he'd never done it before.

1017
01:13:40,834 --> 01:13:42,836
My dog never bit before.

1018
01:13:44,754 --> 01:13:47,382
But I didn't concern myself with that.

1019
01:13:48,508 --> 01:13:49,884
I went out there with my rifle

1020
01:13:49,968 --> 01:13:52,512
and grabbed his collar
and blew his brains out.

1021
01:13:53,847 --> 01:13:54,973
Is Coffey guilty?

1022
01:13:57,976 --> 01:13:59,686
Yes, he is.

1023
01:14:00,186 --> 01:14:01,187
Don't you doubt it.

1024
01:14:02,314 --> 01:14:04,858
And don't you turn your back on him.

1025
01:14:05,650 --> 01:14:07,100
You may get away with it once

1026
01:14:07,527 --> 01:14:09,529
or even a hundred times.

1027
01:14:10,655 --> 01:14:12,198
But in the end…

1028
01:14:14,326 --> 01:14:15,869
You'll get bit.

1029
01:14:17,203 --> 01:14:19,453
[MUSIC PLAYING SOFTLY]
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

1030
01:14:28,381 --> 01:14:30,884
Oh, me! Oh, my!

1031
01:14:33,094 --> 01:14:34,845
PAUL: John.

1032
01:14:34,929 --> 01:14:36,222
John.

1033
01:14:37,724 --> 01:14:39,851
I'm smelling me some corn bread.

1034
01:14:40,393 --> 01:14:42,187
It's from my missus.

1035
01:14:45,982 --> 01:14:48,318
She wanted to thank you.

1036
01:14:49,736 --> 01:14:51,112
Thank me for what?

1037
01:14:51,571 --> 01:14:53,073
Well, you know.

1038
01:14:55,575 --> 01:14:56,951
[WHISPERS] For helping me.

1039
01:14:57,702 --> 01:14:59,245
Helping you with what?

1040
01:14:59,913 --> 01:15:01,206
You know.

1041
01:15:03,917 --> 01:15:05,377
Oh…

1042
01:15:07,587 --> 01:15:09,589
Was your missus pleased?

1043
01:15:11,424 --> 01:15:13,093
Several times.

1044
01:15:28,608 --> 01:15:32,112
Oh, John, I can smell that from over here.
I surely can.

1045
01:15:34,948 --> 01:15:37,283
Can I give Del and Mr. Jingles some?

1046
01:15:37,867 --> 01:15:39,660
Well, it's yours, John.

1047
01:15:39,744 --> 01:15:41,496
You can do with it as you please.

1048
01:15:44,499 --> 01:15:48,002
Here. This for Del and Mr. Jingles.

1049
01:15:48,670 --> 01:15:52,382
Hey! What about me?
