02:33:43,423 --> 02:33:45,633
You make any noise, I'm gonna kill her.

2092
02:33:45,717 --> 02:33:48,470
You understand?

2093
02:33:49,096 --> 02:33:50,597
Shh…

2094
02:33:51,473 --> 02:33:52,808
[GRUNTING]

2095
02:33:56,937 --> 02:33:58,271
[COUGHING]

2096
02:34:00,315 --> 02:34:01,608
[PANTING]

2097
02:34:04,528 --> 02:34:05,821
[SOBBING]

2098
02:34:07,155 --> 02:34:10,992
He killed them with they love,
they love for each other.

2099
02:34:12,536 --> 02:34:14,413
Now you see how it is.

2100
02:34:16,039 --> 02:34:18,333
That's the way it is every day.

2101
02:34:19,251 --> 02:34:23,004
That's the way it is all over the world.

2102
02:34:27,551 --> 02:34:29,302
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

2103
02:34:33,598 --> 02:34:35,391
-MAN 1: Percy.
-MAN 2: Percy Wetmore.

2104
02:34:35,475 --> 02:34:36,893
-Percy.
-[MEN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

2105
02:34:36,977 --> 02:34:40,021
MAN 1: Son? Percy. Percy Wetmore.

2106
02:34:41,189 --> 02:34:42,232
MAN 1: Son?

2107
02:34:42,983 --> 02:34:44,609
Son, can you hear me?

2108
02:34:44,693 --> 02:34:46,093
Speak up if you can hear us.

2109
02:34:46,987 --> 02:34:49,739
I think this boy's cheese
slid off his cracker.

2110
02:34:50,073 --> 02:34:51,783
[MEN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

2111
02:34:51,867 --> 02:34:55,036
MAN 2: Percy, I got to
ask you a few questions.

2112
02:34:55,120 --> 02:34:58,331
DEAN: That's right. One minute,
he was fine, and the next, blammo.

2113
02:34:58,415 --> 02:35:00,833
BRUTAL: Dirty bastard grabbed
him through the bars few days back.

2114
02:35:00,917 --> 02:35:02,919
Scared the boy so bad, he wet hisself.

2115
02:35:04,588 --> 02:35:07,340
See, we didn't even...
We didn't see it happen.

2116
02:35:07,424 --> 02:35:09,134
[CONTINUE SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

2117
02:35:11,553 --> 02:35:16,641
I'll cover for you as much as
I can, even if it means my job.

2118
02:35:17,893 --> 02:35:19,644
But I have to know,

2119
02:35:20,270 --> 02:35:21,312
does this have anything to do

2120
02:35:21,396 --> 02:35:23,148
with what happened at my house?

2121
02:35:26,318 --> 02:35:27,819
Does it, Paul?

2122
02:35:29,863 --> 02:35:30,906
No.

2123
02:36:06,274 --> 02:36:08,443
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING ON RADIO]

2124
02:36:35,637 --> 02:36:37,180
[CLICKS TONGUE]

2125
02:36:37,264 --> 02:36:38,473
[SIGHS]

2126
02:36:55,323 --> 02:36:56,616
[TURNS RADIO OFF]

2127
02:36:58,493 --> 02:36:59,661
Does Hal know?

2128
02:37:00,245 --> 02:37:02,330
That Coffey's innocent, I mean.

2129
02:37:03,582 --> 02:37:05,250
Well, can he help?

2130
02:37:05,834 --> 02:37:08,484
Does he have the influence
to do something about this?

2131
02:37:09,004 --> 02:37:10,421
Stop the execution?

2132
02:37:10,505 --> 02:37:11,506
No.

2133
02:37:14,843 --> 02:37:16,761
Then don't tell him.

2134
02:37:16,845 --> 02:37:18,930
If it can't help, don't tell him.

2135
02:37:19,598 --> 02:37:20,682
Ever.

2136
02:37:23,059 --> 02:37:24,644
I won't.

2137
02:37:34,654 --> 02:37:36,155
[SIGHS]

2138
02:37:36,239 --> 02:37:38,617
There's no way out of
this for you, is there?

2139
02:37:40,410 --> 02:37:41,453
No.

2140
02:37:42,537 --> 02:37:45,122
And I've been thinking
about it, believe me.

2141
02:37:45,206 --> 02:37:48,418
I've been running it through
my head any number of ways.

2142
02:37:48,960 --> 02:37:50,003
No.

2143
02:37:51,254 --> 02:37:52,964
I'll tell you the truth, honey.

2144
02:37:54,883 --> 02:37:59,054
I've done some things in my
life that I am not proud of,

2145
02:38:00,221 --> 02:38:04,392
but this is the first time I've
ever felt real danger of hell.

2146
02:38:06,311 --> 02:38:07,395
Hell?

2147
02:38:09,147 --> 02:38:10,565
[WHISPERS] Oh, Paul.

2148
02:38:13,318 --> 02:38:14,736
Talk to him.

2149
02:38:16,154 --> 02:38:17,614
Talk to John.

2150
02:38:19,783 --> 02:38:21,701
Find out what he wants.

2151
02:38:25,705 --> 02:38:27,582
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

2152
02:38:27,666 --> 02:38:29,209
[KEYS JANGLING]

2153
02:38:30,418 --> 02:38:32,128
[CELL DOOR OPENING]

2154
02:38:38,718 --> 02:38:39,761
Hello, boss.

2155
02:38:40,762 --> 02:38:42,138
Hello, John.

2156
02:38:43,515 --> 02:38:45,809
I guess you know
we're coming down to it now.

2157
02:38:46,768 --> 02:38:48,353
Another couple of days.

2158
02:39:01,950 --> 02:39:05,000
Is there anything special you
wanna eat for dinner that night?

2159
02:39:05,453 --> 02:39:07,288
We can rustle you up most anything.

2160
02:39:17,799 --> 02:39:19,759
Meat loaf be nice.

2161
02:39:19,843 --> 02:39:23,763
Mashed taters, gravy. Okra.

2162
02:39:25,390 --> 02:39:28,143
Maybe some of that fine
corn bread your missus make…

2163
02:39:28,977 --> 02:39:30,895
If she don't mind.

2164
02:39:33,314 --> 02:39:34,649
Now, uh…

2165
02:39:35,316 --> 02:39:36,734
What about a preacher?

2166
02:39:36,818 --> 02:39:39,696
Someone to say a little prayer with.

2167
02:39:40,363 --> 02:39:42,282
Don't want no preacher.

2168
02:39:43,658 --> 02:39:46,119
You can say a prayer, if you like.

2169
02:39:46,911 --> 02:39:48,288
Me?

2170
02:39:50,999 --> 02:39:53,543
Suppose I could, if it came to that.

2171
02:39:57,839 --> 02:39:58,923
John…

2172
02:40:01,885 --> 02:40:04,637
I have to ask you
something very important now.

2173
02:40:06,514 --> 02:40:08,516
I know what you gonna say.

2174
02:40:09,184 --> 02:40:10,518
You don't have to say it.

2175
02:40:11,019 --> 02:40:13,730
No, I do. I do. I have to say it.

2176
02:40:15,231 --> 02:40:16,691
John,

2177
02:40:18,359 --> 02:40:20,528
tell me what you want me to do.

2178
02:40:21,571 --> 02:40:23,406
You want me to take you out of here?

2179
02:40:24,741 --> 02:40:26,784
Just let you run away?

2180
02:40:26,868 --> 02:40:28,578
See how far you could get?

2181
02:40:30,371 --> 02:40:32,665
Why would you do such a foolish thing?

2182
02:40:35,001 --> 02:40:37,628
On the day of my judgment,

2183
02:40:37,712 --> 02:40:40,172
when I stand before God

2184
02:40:40,256 --> 02:40:43,551
and he asks me why did I

2185
02:40:44,427 --> 02:40:48,807
did I kill one of his true miracles,

2186
02:40:50,433 --> 02:40:52,352
what am I going to say?

2187
02:40:53,561 --> 02:40:55,271
That it was my job?

2188
02:40:57,732 --> 02:40:59,150
It's my job.

2189
02:40:59,859 --> 02:41:03,863
You tell God the Father
it was a kindness you done.

2190
02:41:07,659 --> 02:41:09,828
I know you're hurting and worrying.

2191
02:41:10,829 --> 02:41:12,830
I can feel it on you.

2192
02:41:12,914 --> 02:41:14,514
But you ought to quit on it now.

2193
02:41:15,583 --> 02:41:18,086
I want it to be over and done with.

2194
02:41:19,379 --> 02:41:20,463
I do.

2195
02:41:22,173 --> 02:41:23,383
[SIGHS]

2196
02:41:25,426 --> 02:41:27,011
I'm tired, boss.

2197
02:41:28,555 --> 02:41:30,431
I'm tired of being on the road,

2198
02:41:30,515 --> 02:41:32,600
lonely as a sparrow in the rain.

2199
02:41:34,269 --> 02:41:37,063
I'm tired of never having me
a buddy to be with,

2200
02:41:37,647 --> 02:41:41,609
to tell me where we's going
to, coming from, or why.

2201
02:41:43,111 --> 02:41:46,823
Mostly, I'm tired of people
being ugly to each other.

2202
02:41:48,283 --> 02:41:52,078
I'm tired of all the pain
I feel and hear in the world,

2203
02:41:52,704 --> 02:41:54,038
every day.

2204
02:41:54,581 --> 02:41:56,457
There's too much of it.

2205
02:41:57,000 --> 02:42:00,128
It's like pieces of glass in my head,

2206
02:42:00,962 --> 02:42:02,422
all the time.

2207
02:42:04,966 --> 02:42:06,676
Can you understand?

2208
02:42:09,679 --> 02:42:12,307
Yes, John, I think I can.

2209
02:42:15,143 --> 02:42:18,193
BRUTAL: Well, there must be
something we can do for you, John.

2210
02:42:20,732 --> 02:42:22,632
There must be something that you want.

2211
02:42:32,327 --> 02:42:35,872
I ain't never seen me a flicker show.

2212
02:42:36,873 --> 02:42:38,541
[MAN SINGING ON SCREEN]

2213
02:44:02,500 --> 02:44:04,585
Why, they's angels.

2214
02:44:05,920 --> 02:44:08,505
Angels, just like up in heaven.

2215
02:44:08,589 --> 02:44:10,258
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

2216
02:44:27,233 --> 02:44:29,110
[KEYS JANGLING]

2217
02:45:09,233 --> 02:45:11,194
It be all right, fellas.

2218
02:45:12,653 --> 02:45:14,697
This here's the hard part.

2219
02:45:16,199 --> 02:45:17,658
I'll be all right in a while.

2220
02:45:18,659 --> 02:45:22,914
John, I should have this just for now.

2221
02:45:27,460 --> 02:45:29,420
I'll give it back after.

2222
02:45:32,757 --> 02:45:37,011
You know, I fell asleep this
afternoon and had me a dream.

2223
02:45:38,846 --> 02:45:40,681
I dreamed about Del's mouse.

2224
02:45:42,100 --> 02:45:43,184
Did you, John?

2225
02:45:43,851 --> 02:45:48,522
I dreamed Mr. Jingles got down to
that place Boss Howell talked about.

2226
02:45:48,606 --> 02:45:50,483
That Mouseville place.

2227
02:45:51,234 --> 02:45:53,402
I dreamed there's kids. [LAUGHS]

2228
02:45:54,195 --> 02:45:57,907
And how they laughed at his tricks.
My! [CONTINUES LAUGHING]

2229
02:45:59,867 --> 02:46:03,329
I dreamed that those two little
blond-headed girls was there.

2230
02:46:04,038 --> 02:46:06,040
They's laughing, too.

2231
02:46:06,124 --> 02:46:09,376
I put my arms around them
and set 'em on my knees.

2232
02:46:09,460 --> 02:46:11,503
And there's no blood
coming out of they hair,

2233
02:46:11,587 --> 02:46:13,589
and they's just fine.

2234
02:46:13,673 --> 02:46:16,801
We all watched
Mr. Jingles roll that spool.

2235
02:46:18,302 --> 02:46:19,595
How we did laugh.

2236
02:46:19,679 --> 02:46:21,430
Fit to bust, we was!

2237
02:46:37,572 --> 02:46:38,698
John.

2238
02:46:39,907 --> 02:46:44,078
[WHISPERING] They's lots
of folks here that hate me. Lots!

2239
02:46:45,913 --> 02:46:47,415
I can feel it.

2240
02:46:48,124 --> 02:46:50,042
It's like bees stinging me.

2241
02:46:50,418 --> 02:46:52,628
Well, feel how we feel, then.

2242
02:46:54,130 --> 02:46:55,214
We don't hate you.

2243
02:46:56,757 --> 02:46:58,217
Can you feel that?

2244
02:47:00,553 --> 02:47:02,471
KLAUS: Kill him twice, you boys!

2245
02:47:03,431 --> 02:47:07,559
You go on and kill that
raping baby killer twice!

2246
02:47:07,643 --> 02:47:09,187
That'd be fine!

2247
02:47:25,995 --> 02:47:28,456
Wipe your face before you stand up, Dean.

2248
02:47:28,873 --> 02:47:30,124
Yes, sir.

2249
02:47:30,917 --> 02:47:32,251
[SNIFFLES]

2250
02:47:32,877 --> 02:47:34,086
[SIGHS]

2251
02:47:42,220 --> 02:47:43,387
Roll on one.

2252
02:47:47,475 --> 02:47:49,143
[MACHINE WHIRRING]

2253
02:47:51,437 --> 02:47:54,815
MARJORIE: Does it hurt yet?
I hope it does.

2254
02:47:55,816 --> 02:47:57,818
I hope it hurts like hell.

2255
02:48:00,071 --> 02:48:01,780
John Coffey, you've been condemned to die

2256
02:48:01,864 --> 02:48:04,032
in the electric chair
by a jury of your peers.

2257
02:48:04,116 --> 02:48:07,953
Sentence imposed by a judge
in good standing in this state.

2258
02:48:08,037 --> 02:48:10,937
Do you have anything to say
before sentence is carried out?

2259
02:48:13,084 --> 02:48:15,044
I'm sorry for what I am.

2260
02:48:27,682 --> 02:48:29,141
Please, boss,

2261
02:48:30,685 --> 02:48:33,145
don't put that thing over my face.

2262
02:48:34,647 --> 02:48:36,649
Don't put me in the dark.

2263
02:48:37,650 --> 02:48:39,860
[WHISPERING] I's afraid of the dark.

2264
02:48:49,954 --> 02:48:51,330
[SOFTLY] All right, John.

2265
02:49:11,726 --> 02:49:14,728
[SINGING SOFTLY] <i>Heaven, I'm in heaven</i>

2266
02:49:14,812 --> 02:49:19,650
<i>Heaven, heaven I'm in heaven</i>

2267
02:49:20,192 --> 02:49:22,737
[WHISPERING] <i>Heaven, heaven</i>

2268
02:49:23,279 --> 02:49:24,739
<i>I'm in heaven</i>

2269
02:49:25,281 --> 02:49:26,782
<i>Heaven</i>

2270
02:49:27,742 --> 02:49:30,244
<i>Heaven, I'm in heaven</i>

2271
02:49:30,828 --> 02:49:35,958
<i>I'm in heaven I'm in heaven I'm in heaven</i>

2272
02:49:36,792 --> 02:49:39,253
<i>Heaven Heaven</i>

2273
02:49:39,962 --> 02:49:41,005
<i>Heaven</i>

2274
02:49:45,843 --> 02:49:47,261
John Coffey,

2275
02:49:48,387 --> 02:49:50,013
electricity shall now be passed

2276
02:49:50,097 --> 02:49:51,682
through your body until you are dead

2277
02:49:51,766 --> 02:49:53,601
in accordance with state law.

2278
02:49:56,270 --> 02:49:59,565
May God have mercy on your soul.

2279
02:50:34,475 --> 02:50:35,518
[WHISPERING] Paul.

2280
02:50:38,729 --> 02:50:40,481
You have to say it.

2281
02:50:42,316 --> 02:50:44,443
You have to give the order.

2282
02:51:02,711 --> 02:51:05,005
JOHN: <i>He killed 'em with they love.</i>

2283
02:51:05,089 --> 02:51:09,176
<i>That's how it is every day
all over the world.</i>

2284
02:51:23,691 --> 02:51:25,234
[SHAKILY] Roll on two.

2285
02:51:26,819 --> 02:51:28,362
[ELECTRICITY SIZZLING]

2286
02:53:09,880 --> 02:53:12,550
PAUL: <i>It was the last
execution I ever took part in.</i>

2287
02:53:13,425 --> 02:53:16,052
I just couldn't do it anymore after that.

2288
02:53:16,136 --> 02:53:19,389
Brutal either. We both transferred out,

2289
02:53:19,473 --> 02:53:22,393
took jobs with Boys' Correctional.

2290
02:53:23,269 --> 02:53:24,895
It was all right.

2291
02:53:25,729 --> 02:53:28,232
"Catch them young" became my motto.

2292
02:53:31,819 --> 02:53:33,112
You don't believe me.

2293
02:53:33,904 --> 02:53:36,532
I don't imagine you'd lie to me, Paul.

2294
02:53:37,157 --> 02:53:41,370
It's just that... It's quite a story.

2295
02:53:42,246 --> 02:53:44,706
One thing I don't understand.

2296
02:53:44,790 --> 02:53:50,004
You said you and Jan
had a grown son in 1935.

2297
02:53:50,588 --> 02:53:52,089
Is that right?

2298
02:53:52,548 --> 02:53:54,508
The math doesn't work, does it?

2299
02:54:00,180 --> 02:54:02,516
Do you feel up to taking a walk?

2300
02:54:03,183 --> 02:54:04,810
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

2301
02:54:23,412 --> 02:54:24,663
PAUL: Watch your step.

2302
02:54:25,414 --> 02:54:27,416
Now let your eyes adjust.

2303
02:54:39,553 --> 02:54:40,721
There.

2304
02:54:43,223 --> 02:54:47,061
Hey. Wake up, old fella. Wake up.

2305
02:54:51,065 --> 02:54:54,818
Paul, it isn't. It can't be.

2306
02:54:59,323 --> 02:55:00,741
Come over here, boy.

2307
02:55:01,367 --> 02:55:03,577
Come on over here and see this lady.

2308
02:55:06,580 --> 02:55:09,249
That can't be Mr. Jingles.

2309
02:55:15,381 --> 02:55:17,132
[SPEAKING IN FRENCH]

2310
02:55:32,189 --> 02:55:34,108
Go on, you can do it.

2311
02:55:41,782 --> 02:55:45,661
This isn't exactly the
Mouseville we had in mind, is it?

2312
02:55:47,121 --> 02:55:50,416
But we make do. Don't we, old fella?

2313
02:55:57,506 --> 02:56:00,426
I think Mr. Jingles happened by accident.

2314
02:56:01,677 --> 02:56:06,056
I think when we electrocuted
Del, and it all went so badly…

2315
02:56:06,640 --> 02:56:08,892
Well, John could feel that, you know.

2316
02:56:09,393 --> 02:56:11,979
And I think a part of

2317
02:56:13,063 --> 02:56:15,732
whatever magic was inside of him

2318
02:56:15,816 --> 02:56:18,485
just leapt into my tiny friend here.

2319
02:56:20,362 --> 02:56:21,989
As for me,

2320
02:56:23,449 --> 02:56:25,909
John had to give me a part of himself,

2321
02:56:26,452 --> 02:56:28,745
a gift, the way he saw it,

2322
02:56:28,829 --> 02:56:31,790
so that I could see for myself
what Wild Bill had done.

2323
02:56:34,668 --> 02:56:36,420
When John did that…

2324
02:56:38,464 --> 02:56:40,257
When he took my hand,

2325
02:56:41,759 --> 02:56:43,510
a part of the power

2326
02:56:44,094 --> 02:56:45,679
that worked through him

2327
02:56:46,513 --> 02:56:48,098
spilled into me.

2328
02:56:48,932 --> 02:56:50,184
He what?

2329
02:56:51,018 --> 02:56:54,646
He infected you with life?

2330
02:56:56,190 --> 02:56:58,275
It's as good a word as any.

2331
02:56:59,985 --> 02:57:04,031
He infected us both, didn't he, Mr.
Jingles? With life.

2332
02:57:08,702 --> 02:57:11,038
I'm 108 years old, Elaine.

2333
02:57:11,997 --> 02:57:15,542
I was 44 the year that John
Coffey walked the Green Mile.

2334
02:57:19,213 --> 02:57:21,131
You mustn't blame John.

2335
02:57:21,673 --> 02:57:23,133
He couldn't help what happened.

2336
02:57:23,217 --> 02:57:26,512
He was... He's just a force of nature.

2337
02:57:28,096 --> 02:57:31,892
Oh, I've lived to see
some amazing things, Ellie.

2338
02:57:33,519 --> 02:57:35,729
Another century come to pass.

2339
02:57:36,730 --> 02:57:38,065
But I've…

2340
02:57:39,274 --> 02:57:43,445
I've had to see my friends and
loved ones die off through the years.

2341
02:57:44,196 --> 02:57:45,781
Hal and Melinda,

2342
02:57:46,615 --> 02:57:50,410
Brutus Howell, my wife, my boy.

2343
02:57:53,872 --> 02:57:55,457
And you, Elaine.

2344
02:57:56,792 --> 02:57:58,418
You'll die, too.

2345
02:57:59,962 --> 02:58:03,674
And my curse is knowing
that I'll be there to see it.

2346
02:58:05,884 --> 02:58:07,970
It's my atonement, you see.

2347
02:58:08,887 --> 02:58:10,556
It's my punishment

2348
02:58:10,848 --> 02:58:13,433
for letting John Coffey
ride the lightning,

2349
02:58:15,227 --> 02:58:17,437
<i>for killing a miracle of God.</i>

2350
02:58:19,356 --> 02:58:21,775
PRIEST: <i>Almighty, everlasting God,</i>

2351
02:58:22,651 --> 02:58:24,611
the source of all being and life…

2352
02:58:25,362 --> 02:58:29,116
PAUL: <i>You'll be gone like all the others.
I'll have to stay.</i>

2353
02:58:31,535 --> 02:58:34,997
<i>Oh, I'll die eventually.
Of that I'm sure.</i>

2354
02:58:36,331 --> 02:58:39,459
<i>I have no illusions of immortality.</i>

2355
02:58:40,627 --> 02:58:42,963
<i>But I will have wished for death</i>

2356
02:58:43,630 --> 02:58:45,716
<i>long before death finds me.</i>

2357
02:58:47,384 --> 02:58:50,345
<i>In truth, I wish for it already.</i>

2358
02:58:50,429 --> 02:58:52,639
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING ON RADIO]

2359
02:58:56,977 --> 02:58:58,604
[SOFT SQUEAKING]

2360
02:59:03,233 --> 02:59:04,651
Mr. Jingles?

2361
02:59:14,161 --> 02:59:15,954
Where you been, hmm?

2362
02:59:16,705 --> 02:59:20,834
Been worried about you, boy.
You hungry, hmm?

2363
02:59:20,918 --> 02:59:23,418
Let's go see if we can't
find you something to eat.

2364
02:59:24,504 --> 02:59:26,256
A few crumbs anyway.

2365
02:59:26,340 --> 02:59:28,258
I know you'd like that.

2366
02:59:29,551 --> 02:59:31,553
Look at you. Mr. Jingles.

2367
02:59:32,638 --> 02:59:35,849
<i>I lie in bed most nights
thinking about it.</i>

2368
02:59:36,683 --> 02:59:38,060
<i>And I wait.</i>

2369
02:59:39,353 --> 02:59:42,438
<i>I think about all the people I've loved,</i>

2370
02:59:42,522 --> 02:59:44,024
<i>now long gone.</i>

2371
02:59:45,484 --> 02:59:47,986
<i>I think about my beautiful Jan,</i>

2372
02:59:48,070 --> 02:59:50,489
<i>how I lost her so many years ago.</i>

2373
02:59:52,366 --> 02:59:57,412
<i>And I think about all of us
walking our own Green Mile,</i>

2374
02:59:57,496 --> 02:59:59,289
<i>each in our own time.</i>

2375
03:00:01,083 --> 03:00:04,210
<i>But one thought more than any other</i>

2376
03:00:04,294 --> 03:00:06,380
<i>keeps me awake most nights.</i>

2377
03:00:08,173 --> 03:00:11,426
<i>If he could make a mouse live so long,</i>

2378
03:00:12,678 --> 03:00:14,721
<i>how much longer do I have?</i>

2379
03:00:19,142 --> 03:00:21,561
<i>We each owe a death.</i>

2380
03:00:22,145 --> 03:00:24,106
<i>There are no exceptions.</i>

2381
03:00:25,357 --> 03:00:26,817
<i>But, oh, God,</i>

2382
03:00:28,402 --> 03:00:30,070
<i>sometimes,</i>

2383
03:00:30,696 --> 03:00:33,532
<i>the Green Mile seems so long.</i>

